{
  "texts": [
    "Using Einstein's formula for the deflection (Saha et al. 2024) the lens equation due to N compact masses M i in the presence of a mass sheet κ c and shear γ = γ 2 1 + γ 2 2 becomes:",
    "For a homogeneous mass distribution with surface density κ *, the second term becomes ∝ -κ * θ.",
    "This equation can also be written as:",
    "where we used the Einstein radii θ Ei of the compact objects in the lens plane (Saha et al. 2024).",
    "This is a fundamental quantity for microlensing as it defines the scale length of the phenomenon."
  ]
}